messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Help me.
Hi, what's going on?
Help me. My son is missing. I'm going crazy.
Okay, you're going to have to calm down. What address are you at?
13604 Sunrise Red. Would you help me? Please help me.
How old is he?
He's five. My God, where's my son?
What color shirt is he wearing?
Black shirt. He's lost.
What color pants?
I don't know.
What's your name?
Nadia. Please help me.
How long has it been since you've seen him?
About half an hour ago.
Where was he the last time you saw him?
He was out front.
Are your neighbors helping you look for him?
Yeah, they don't see him anywhere.
Did you go in the house to see if he went in to hide?
He's nowhere in the house or the back.
Does he have any siblings?
Yes, he has brothers and sisters.
Has he ever done this before?
No, never.
Was the two-year-old with him?
No, he was wearing a black shirt.
So he was playing by himself in the front yard?
Yes, his older brother was there too.
How old is the older brother?
He's seven.
And did you ask the older brother if he's seen him?
Yes, I did. He hasn't seen him.
Okay, and that's your address: 13604 Sunrise Red?
Yes, please help me.
Don't worry, we're sending help. Just stay calm.
What if someone took him?
Let's not jump to conclusions. Have you checked inside the house thoroughly?
Yes, he's not there.
Try to stay calm for your other children, okay?
Okay, I will.
Wait, he's back! He walked back home!
He's back? Are you sure?
Yes, he's here!
Alright, stay calm. Is he okay?
Yes, he seems fine. Thank you.
Good. We're still sending someone to check on you. Stay safe.
